Hey Daniel, sorry for the delay in getting back to you on this. After some digging, this seems like purely a user error on my part. Really not sure where I got this mixed up, so thanks again for pointing it out.

I believe the correct type for that param on `customBodyRender` should be [`MUIDataTableData['data'][number]`](https://github.com/Patrick-Erichsen/DefinitelyTyped/blob/dfe100fab161218fdff903e270984dd46d6537a4/types/mui-datatables/index.d.ts#L28) (i.e. `object | number[] | string[]`).

```ts
export interface MUIDataTableData {
    data: Array<object | number[] | string[]>;
    index: number;
}

...

export interface MUIDataTableColumnOptions {
    customBodyRender?: (
        value: MUIDataTableData['data'][number],
        tableMeta: MUIDataTableMeta,
        updateValue: (value: string) => void,
    ) => string | React.ReactNode;
    ....
}
```

If this looks good to you, let me know and I can open up [this pull request I have ready](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/compare/master...Patrick-Erichsen:pe-mui-datatables-fix?expand=1#diff-13e6d38691187d88542504b110fd099bR177).

<hr />

**Edit:** That reply above actually doesn't look quite right given that a `number` or `boolean` doesn't fit into `object | number[] | string[]`. I am not seeing any types that would correspond here. 

I'm not opposed to just reverting it back to `any` - I tried digging around in the source code a bit as well and haven't had luck discerning what the appropriate type should be.
